[[ja:若狭彦神社]]
[[zh:若狭彦神社]]

'''Wakasahiko Shrine''' (若狭彦神社, ''Wakasahiko jinja'') is a [[Shinto]] shrine located in [[Obama, Fukui]] Prefecture, Japan. It was established in 714, and is divided into an upper shrine (Wakasahiko Shrine) and lower shrine (Wakasahime Shrine, 若狭姫神社). The upper shrine's main festival is held annually on October 10; the lower shrine's is held on March 10. Kami enshrined here include [[Hoori]] no mikoto and [[Toyotamahime]].
It was formerly an imperial shrine of the first rank (国幣中社, ''kokuhei chusha'') in the [[Modern system of ranked Shinto Shrines]]. It was also the [[ichinomiya]] of [[Wakasa Province]].
